  <section>
    <title>MDMI SEER &amp; SOLOR: Similarities</title>          
    <itemizedlist mark='bullet' spacing='compact'>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                Both SEER and SOLOR are open source.
              </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                Both SEER and SOLOR have unambiguous, unique atomic concepts.
              </para>
            </listitem>
            
		        <listitem>
              <para>
                Both SEER and SOLOR are extensible, with local and shared extensions that can be added if the desired concept does not already exist.
              </para>
            </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>
   </section>
   <section>
    <title>Our Need</title>       
      <itemizedlist mark='bullet' spacing='compact'>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                The initial driver for MDMI Version 2.0 was based on experience: the description of a business element used in MDMI was the only resource for understanding the meaning of the business element. Descriptions are subject to interpretation.
              </para>
			       <itemizedlist mark='bullet' spacing='compact'>
			           <listitem>
			               <para>
				                  Example 1 – Industry Standards Experiences. HL7 projects.
				            </para>
			           </listitem>
			           <listitem>
			               <para>
				                Example 2 – Transformations between existing implementations experiences. IPO and HIE projects. 
			               </para>
			           </listitem>
			         </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>
			      <listitem>
              <para>
			           Bottom Line: 
			         </para>
			           <itemizedlist mark='bullet' spacing='compact'>
			               <listitem>
			                   <para>
				                    There can be data quality issues in transformations using current practices.
			                   </para>
			               </listitem>
			           </itemizedlist>
              </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
  </section>
<section>
    <title>Our Need</title>       
          <itemizedlist mark='bullet' spacing='compact'>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                The plan for MDMI 2.0 is to use SOLOR as the Reference Model to add Semantic Concepts for each Business Element in the SEER to provide a unique, post-coordinated description.
              </para> 
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
  </section>
   <section>
    <title>MDMI 2.0</title>   
	  <itemizedlist mark='bullet' spacing='compact'>
         <listitem>
              <para>
                The plan for MDMI 2.0 is to use SOLOR as the Reference Model to add Semantic Concepts for each Business Element in the SEER to provide a unique, post-coordinated description. 
              </para>
			   </listitem>
         <listitem>
			      <itemizedlist mark='bullet' spacing='compact'>
			        <listitem>
				        <para>
				          The business elements in MDMI 2.0 will have post-coordinated concepts linked to the semantic concepts in SOLOR.
			           </para>
			         </listitem>
			       <listitem>
			             <para>
				              SOLOR provides a harmonized understanding of many industry standard healthcare ontologies &amp; terminologies
			             </para>
			       </listitem>
			      </itemizedlist>
          </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
